        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">2.7</div>
          <div class="ins-text"><strong>Test the CTO Agent:</strong> Prompt it — <em>"Give me the Azure Function architecture for MCP-01 (Financial Data Ingestion) using Python, pdfplumber, and Supabase. Include security considerations for ISM compliance."</em> Evaluate depth and structure of output before proceeding.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 3 -->

  <div class="step-block">
    <div class="step-header">
      <div class="step-num-box">3</div>
      <div class="step-title-wrap">
        <div class="step-title">Create the CIO Agent</div>
        <div class="step-subtitle">Sales, marketing &amp; commercial intelligence · Claude Sonnet 4.6</div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-agent-badge badge-cio">CIO AGENT</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <div class="step-instructions">
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">3.1</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Create <strong>New Agent</strong>. Name: <code>Dhruva CIO</code>. Description: <code>Sales strategy, marketing content, partner pipeline, client relationships.</code></div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">3.2</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Set LLM to <code>claude-primary</code>, model <code>claude-sonnet-4-6</code>. Temperature: <code>0.6</code> (slightly higher for creative commercial output). Max tokens: <code>4000</code>.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">3.3</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Paste the <strong>CIO System Prompt</strong> from the Agent Configs tab. Add: <code>You have access to the Dhruva knowledge base including the current partner list and client pipeline. Check it when asked about specific firms or contacts.</code></div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">3.4</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Enable <strong>Tools</strong>: Web search (for researching accounting firms and prospects), Gmail draft tool (if n8n Gmail integration is active), Google Calendar read access.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">3.5</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Set <strong>Sub-agent permissions</strong>: CIO can delegate to <code>Dhruva Content</code> and <code>Dhruva Outreach</code> agents.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">3.6</div>
          <div class="ins-text"><strong>Test the CIO Agent:</strong> Prompt — <em>"I have a meeting next week with the managing partner of a 15-person accounting firm in Sydney. They have 40 business clients. Draft me a 3-touch outreach sequence and a meeting agenda."</em> Evaluate commercial sharpness.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 4 -->

  <div class="step-block">
    <div class="step-header">
      <div class="step-num-box">4</div>
      <div class="step-title-wrap">
        <div class="step-title">Create Sub-Agents (Dev, QA, Content, Outreach)</div>
        <div class="step-subtitle">4 agents · GPT-4o-mini + Gemini Flash</div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-agent-badge badge-all">SUB-AGENTS</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <div class="step-instructions">
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">4.1</div>
          <div class="ins-text"><strong>Dev Agent:</strong> New Agent → Name: <code>Dhruva Dev</code>. LLM: <code>openai-mini</code> / <code>gpt-4o-mini</code>. Temperature: <code>0.1</code>. Max tokens: <code>4000</code>. Paste Dev Agent system prompt. Tools: code interpreter, file read/write. No sub-agent permissions.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">4.2</div>
          <div class="ins-text"><strong>QA Agent:</strong> New Agent → Name: <code>Dhruva QA</code>. LLM: <code>openai-mini</code> / <code>gpt-4o-mini</code>. Temperature: <code>0.1</code>. Paste QA system prompt. Tools: file read. Receives outputs from Dev Agent and client report drafts.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">4.3</div>
          <div class="ins-text"><strong>Content Agent:</strong> New Agent → Name: <code>Dhruva Content</code>. LLM: <code>gemini-flash</code>. Temperature: <code>0.7</code>. Max tokens: <code>2000</code>. Paste Content Agent system prompt. No tools required — pure text generation.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">4.4</div>
          <div class="ins-text"><strong>Outreach Agent:</strong> New Agent → Name: <code>Dhruva Outreach</code>. LLM: <code>openai-mini</code>. Temperature: <code>0.4</code>. Max tokens: <code>1500</code>. Paste Outreach system prompt. Tool: Gmail draft via n8n HTTP webhook.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">4.5</div>
          <div class="ins-text">For each sub-agent, <strong>set the parent agent</strong> in permissions: Dev + QA → parent is CTO. Content + Outreach → parent is CIO. This enforces the chain of command and prevents agents from being called directly without context.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout">
        <div class="callout-icon">✦</div>
        <div class="callout-text"><strong>Delegation pattern:</strong> You talk to CTO or CIO. They talk to their sub-agents. Sub-agents return results to their parent. You never prompt Dev, QA, Content, or Outreach directly — unless it's a quick test. This keeps context clean and outputs consistent.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 5 -->

  <div class="step-block">
    <div class="step-header">
      <div class="step-num-box">5</div>
      <div class="step-title-wrap">
        <div class="step-title">Connect n8n Automation Workflows</div>
        <div class="step-subtitle">Link agents to your existing n8n instance for automated triggers</div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-agent-badge badge-cto">CTO + CIO</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <div class="step-instructions">
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">5.1</div>
          <div class="ins-text">In n8n, create a webhook node — <strong>"Paperclip Inbound"</strong>. This receives task briefs from Paperclip agents via HTTP POST. The CTO and CIO agents call this when they need to trigger an automated workflow (e.g. send report, process statement).</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">5.2</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Build <strong>Workflow 1 — Monthly Report Trigger:</strong> Schedule node (1st of month, 6am AEST) → Paperclip HTTP call → CTO Agent generates client report → QA Agent validates → n8n sends PDF via Gmail to client.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">5.3</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Build <strong>Workflow 2 — Risk Alert:</strong> n8n polls ATO/ASIC RSS daily → if new item matches client profile keywords → sends to MCP-04 Azure Function → Claude analyses → if severity ≥3, n8n sends alert to client via Telegram + Email.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">5.4</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Build <strong>Workflow 3 — New Lead Handoff:</strong> dhruva.ai contact form → n8n → formats lead data → sends to CIO Agent via Paperclip → CIO generates qualification brief + outreach email draft → sends to Gaurav for review via Telegram.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">5.5</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Build <strong>Workflow 4 — Weekly CIO Review:</strong> Every Monday 8am → n8n triggers CIO Agent → "Generate this week's commercial priorities: pipeline status, content to publish, outreach follow-ups due" → sends summary to Gaurav via Telegram.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="code-block"><span class="comment"># Sample n8n Paperclip call (HTTP Request node)</span>
<span class="key">Method:</span> <span class="val">POST</span>
<span class="key">URL:</span> <span class="val">https://paperclip.ing/api/agents/dhruva-cio/message</span>
<span class="key">Auth:</span> <span class="val">Bearer {{$env.PAPERCLIP_API_KEY}}</span>
<span class="key">Body:</span>
{
  <span class="str">"message"</span>: <span class="str">"Weekly commercial review: Summarise pipeline status and top 3 priorities for this week."</span>,
  <span class="str">"context"</span>: {
    <span class="str">"date"</span>: <span class="str">"{{$today}}"</span>,
    <span class="str">"trigger"</span>: <span class="str">"weekly_automated_review"</span>
  }
}</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 6 -->

  <div class="step-block">
    <div class="step-header">
      <div class="step-num-box">6</div>
      <div class="step-title-wrap">
        <div class="step-title">Your Daily Operating Rhythm</div>
        <div class="step-subtitle">How to actually work with the agent network each day</div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-agent-badge badge-all">GAURAV</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <div class="step-instructions">
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">MON</div>
          <div class="ins-text"><strong>8am:</strong> Receive CIO weekly brief via Telegram (auto-triggered by n8n Workflow 4). Review pipeline, approve content queue, send 1 outreach email drafted by Outreach Agent. <strong>Time: 20 minutes.</strong></div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">DAILY</div>
          <div class="ins-text"><strong>When technical work is needed:</strong> Open Paperclip → CTO Agent → describe the task. CTO breaks it down, delegates to Dev/QA, returns result. You review, approve, ship. <strong>No context-switching to code editors for routine tasks.</strong></div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">DAILY</div>
          <div class="ins-text"><strong>When commercial work is needed:</strong> Open Paperclip → CIO Agent → describe the situation. "I have a meeting with X firm tomorrow. Prep me." CIO generates agenda, background, talking points, and a follow-up email draft. <strong>Time: 5 minutes vs 45.</strong></div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">WED</div>
          <div class="ins-text"><strong>Content review:</strong> Content Agent publishes LinkedIn post drafts to a review queue every Wednesday. You spend 10 minutes editing and approving. Scheduler posts Thursday morning (peak accounting professional engagement time).</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">FRI</div>
          <div class="ins-text"><strong>Week close:</strong> Ask CTO Agent — "What's the build status on MCP-02? What's blocking?" Receive structured status report. Update your own notes. Set next week's priorities for both agents. <strong>15 minutes. You stay the director, not the doer.</strong></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="callout">
        <div class="callout-icon">✦</div>
        <div class="callout-text"><strong>The rule:</strong> If a task takes you more than 5 minutes to think about how to start, it belongs in Paperclip. If you've written the same type of document more than twice, the agent should have a template for it. Your job is <strong>direction, relationships, and closing</strong> — not production.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- STEP 7 -->

  <div class="step-block">
    <div class="step-header">
      <div class="step-num-box">7</div>
      <div class="step-title-wrap">
        <div class="step-title">First 30 Days — Execution Sequence</div>
        <div class="step-subtitle">Ordered task list to get from setup to first revenue</div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-agent-badge badge-all">LAUNCH</div>
    </div>
    <div class="step-body">
      <div class="step-instructions">
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">DAY 1–3</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Complete Paperclip setup (Steps 1–4). Test all 6 agents with the prompts specified. <strong>Do not proceed until CTO and CIO agents produce output you'd be comfortable showing a client.</strong> Refine system prompts if needed.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">DAY 4–7</div>
          <div class="ins-text">CTO Agent: complete MCP-02 BAS Agent. Prompt: <em>"Give me the full Python implementation for the BAS GST engine and anomaly detection module per the technical spec."</em> Dev Agent builds. QA Agent validates. You review.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">DAY 8–10</div>
          <div class="ins-text">CIO Agent: generate the Partner Program outreach sequence and one-page brief. Prompt: <em>"Create a 3-touch email sequence for accounting firm partners, offering 3-month free trial of MCP-02 in exchange for testimonial and one client intro."</em></div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">DAY 11–14</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Content Agent: generate first 4 LinkedIn posts. CIO briefs Content Agent. Posts scheduled via n8n. dhruva.ai landing page live with CTO-built demo and CIO-written copy.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">DAY 15–21</div>
          <div class="ins-text">Send Partner Program outreach to 5 accounting firms. Outreach Agent drafts, you personalise each in &lt;2 minutes, you send. n8n tracks opens and triggers follow-up sequence at day 4 if no reply.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="instruction">
          <div class="ins-marker">DAY 22–30</div>
          <div class="ins-text">First accounting firm partner signed. Run their first client through MCP-01 + MCP-02. QA Agent validates output. CIO Agent drafts the results summary. You deliver. First revenue in.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>

<script>
function show(id) {
  document.querySelectorAll('.section').forEach(s => s.classList.remove('active'));
  document.querySelectorAll('.nav-tab').forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'));
  document.getElementById(id).classList.add('active');
  event.target.classList.add('active');
  window.scrollTo({ top: 0, behavior: 'smooth' });
}
</script>

</body>
